## Promotion Pathways

Knowledge flows up the tiers as it earns durability.

| From                      | To                                                                        | When                                                                                                               | Who                               |
| ------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | --------------------------------- |
| `lessons.md` entry        | Tier 2 rule (`.prism/rules/`) or Tier 3 architect (`.prism/architect/`) | When a lesson has fired more than once — the same correction landed in a second session                            | Any agent proposes; human accepts |
| Plan `## Decisions` entry | Tier 3 architect (`.prism/architect/`)                                   | At ticket close — if the decision describes lasting system behavior, not ticket-tactical implementation            | Winston at close-of-ticket        |
| Recurring ad-hoc pattern  | Tier 2 rule (`.prism/rules/`)                                            | When the same clarification appears in review feedback repeatedly — the rule prevents the same class of comment    | Any agent proposes; human accepts |
| Cross-skill drift         | Tier 1 constitution (`AGENTS.md`) + ADR                                   | When the same framework choice needs to be made consistently across skills (e.g. "authors ship, reviewers review") | Human team lead, with ADR         |

**Downward flow** — when a Tier 1 or Tier 2 decision changes, audit the lower tiers for references that need updating. Cross-reference pass at the end of the change PR.

